Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.38,0:01:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.50,0:01:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not supposed to be up here,\Nlooking at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.82,0:01:19.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l just wanted to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.06,0:01:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you're old enough, l suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.22,0:01:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should know the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.46,0:01:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.54,0:01:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt was 1832.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.50,0:01:38.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On a night much like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.30,0:01:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Charles Carroll was the last surviving\Nsigner of the Declaration of lndependence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.06,0:01:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was also a member\Nof a secret society known as the Masons.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.18,0:01:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he knew he was dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.74,0:02:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He woke up his stable boy\Nin the middle of the night
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.22,0:02:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and ordered him to take him to\Nthe White House to see Andrew Jackson,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.78,0:02:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because it was urgent\Nthat he speak to the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.78,0:02:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he talk to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.61,0:02:15.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. He never got the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.54,0:02:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The president wasn't there that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.22,0:02:22.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Charles Carroll had a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.30,0:02:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he took into his confidence\Nthe one person he could,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.46,0:02:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my grandfather's grandfather,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.06,0:02:31.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thomas Gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.86,0:02:33.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was the secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.70,0:02:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.70,0:02:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A treasure beyond all imagining.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.58,0:02:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A treasure that had been\Nfought over for centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.70,0:02:53.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by tyrants, pharaohs,\Nemperors, warlords.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.22,0:02:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And every time it changed hands\Nit grew larger.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.42,0:03:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.22,0:03:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.98,0:03:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt didn't reappear\Nfor more than a thousand years,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.06,0:03:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when knights from the First Crusade
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.90,0:03:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,discovered secret vaults\Nbeneath the Temple of Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.30,0:03:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see, the knights who found the vaults
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.78,0:03:21.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,believed that the treasure\Nwas too great for any one man -
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.06,0:03:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,not even a king.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.06,0:03:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They brought the treasure back to Europe\Nand took the name ''the Knights Templar''.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.50,0:03:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over the next century\Nthey smuggled it out of Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.54,0:03:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they formed a new brotherhood\Ncalled the Freemasons,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.42,0:03:40.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in honour of\Nthe builders of the great temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.42,0:03:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,War followed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.90,0:03:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the time of the American Revolution\Nthe treasure had been hidden again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.78,0:03:49.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By then the Masons included
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.94,0:03:53.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,George Washington,\NBenjamin Franklin, Paul Revere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.86,0:03:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They knew they had to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.70,0:03:59.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the treasure would never fall\Ninto the hands of the British.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.06,0:04:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So they devised a series of clues\Nand maps to its location.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.10,0:04:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over time the clues were lost or forgotten,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.86,0:04:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,until only one remained -
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.02,0:04:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that was the secret that Charles Carroll\Nentrusted to young Thomas Gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.62,0:04:21.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Charlotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.41,0:04:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''The secret lies with Charlotte.''
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.42,0:04:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's Charlotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.22,0:04:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, not even Mr Carroll knew that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.82,0:04:33.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now look here, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.62,0:04:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Freemasons\Namong our Founding Fathers left us clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.94,0:04:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.46,0:04:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The unfinished pyramid.\NThe all-seeing eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.10,0:04:47.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Symbols of the Knights Templar,\Nguardians of the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.90,0:04:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- They're speaking to us through these.\N- You mean laughing at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.90,0:04:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what that dollar represents?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.66,0:04:58.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The entire Gates family fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.22,0:05:02.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Six generations of fools...\Nchasing after fool's gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.50,0:05:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's not about the money, Patrick.\Nlt's never been about the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.86,0:05:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, son. Time to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.54,0:05:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can... say your goodbyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.38,0:05:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.98,0:05:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we knights?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.54,0:05:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.94,0:05:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Um... kneel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.42,0:05:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Benjamin Franklin Gates,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.30,0:05:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you take upon yourself the duty\Nof the Templars, the Freemasons
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.78,0:05:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the family Gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.30,0:05:57.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you so swear?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.34,0:05:59.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l so swear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.94,0:06:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l was thinking about\NHenson and Peary,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.26,0:06:27.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,crossing this kind of terrain with nothing\Nmore than dog sleds and on foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.74,0:06:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Can you imagine?\N- lt's extraordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.10,0:06:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We getting closer?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.06,0:06:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming Ben's theory's correct\Nand my tracking model's accurate,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.98,0:06:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we should be getting very close.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.66,0:06:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't go by me -\Nl broke a shoelace this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.26,0:06:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- lt's... it's a bad omen.\N- Shall we turn around and go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.86,0:06:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or we could pull over\Nand just throw him out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.70,0:07:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.94,0:07:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Riley, you're not missing that little\Nwindowless cubicle we found you in?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.50,0:07:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no. Absolutely not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.90,0:07:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are we stopping?\Nl thought we were looking for a ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.70,0:07:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- l don't see any ship.\N- She's out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.42,0:07:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look... this is a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.82,0:07:46.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could a ship wind up way out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.78,0:07:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, l'm no expert, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.90,0:07:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it could be that the hydrothermic properties\Nof this region
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.94,0:07:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,produce hurricane-force ice storms
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.50,0:07:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that cause the ocean to freeze\Nand then melt and then refreeze,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.50,0:08:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,resulting in a semisolid\Nmigrating land mass
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.02,0:08:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that would land a ship right around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.54,0:08:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.18,0:09:07.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have Viktor\Ncheck the fuel in the generators.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.90,0:09:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two years ago, if you hadn't shown up,\Nhadn't believed the treasure was real,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.66,0:09:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}l don't know\Nif l ever would have found Charlotte.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.98,0:09:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You would have found it, l have no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.70,0:09:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why l didn't think it was\Nas crazy an investment as everyone said.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.26,0:09:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm just relieved that l'm not as crazy\Nas everyone says. Or said my dad was.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.70,0:09:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or my granddad. Or my great-granddad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.26,0:09:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.06,0:09:34.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.78,0:09:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Let's go find some treasure.\N- Yeah, bring us back something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.86,0:10:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, God!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.78,0:10:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You handled that well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.58,0:10:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.30,0:10:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's the cargo hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.98,0:10:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think it's in the barrels?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.70,0:11:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gunpowder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.34,0:11:07.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.10,0:11:15.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would the captain\Nbe guarding this barrel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.46,0:11:41.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l found something!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.70,0:11:49.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.38,0:12:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you guys know what this is?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.98,0:12:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ls it a billion-dollar pipe?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.90,0:12:16.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's a meerschaum pipe.\NAh, that is beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.26,0:12:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the intricacy of the scrollwork\Non the stem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.62,0:12:23.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- ls it a million-dollar pipe?\N- No, it's a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.70,0:12:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.30,0:12:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, don't break it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.50,0:12:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are one step closer to the treasure,\Ngentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.10,0:12:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ben, l thought you said that\Nthe treasure would be on the Charlotte.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.66,0:12:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No, ''The secret lies with Charlotte. ''{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.18,0:12:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l said it could be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.34,0:12:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's Templar symbols.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.10,0:13:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''The legend writ.''
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.14,0:13:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''The stain effected.''
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.26,0:13:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''The key in Silence undetected.''
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.74,0:13:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Fifty-five in iron pen.''
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.66,0:13:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Mr Matlack can't offend.''
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.42,0:13:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's a riddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.54,0:13:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l need to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.58,0:13:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''The legend writ.''
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.58,0:13:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''The stain effected.''
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.34,0:13:38.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What legend?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.22,0:13:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's the legend of the Templar treasure,\Nand the stain effects the legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.42,0:13:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.50,0:13:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''The key in Silence undetected.''
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.78,0:13:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.54,0:13:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The legend and the key...\NNow there's something.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.50,0:13:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A map.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.98,0:13:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maps have legends, maps have keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.74,0:14:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's a map, an invisible map.\NSo now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.90,0:14:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute. What do you mean,\N''invisible'' - ''an invisible map''?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.50,0:14:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''The stain effected''\Ncould refer to a dye or a reagent
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.70,0:14:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,used to bring about a certain result.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.22,0:14:14.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Combined with\N''The key in Silence undetected'',
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.02,0:14:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the implication is that the effect is to make\Nwhat was undetectable detectable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.54,0:14:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless...\N''The key in Silence'' could be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.62,0:14:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.86,0:14:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Albuquerque.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.54,0:14:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See, l can do it too.\NSnorkel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.14,0:14:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's where the map is.\NLike he said, ''Fifty-five in iron pen.''
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.86,0:14:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''lron pen'' is a prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.34,0:14:41.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or it could be, since the primary writing\Nmedium of the time was iron gall ink,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.62,0:14:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the ''pen'' is... just a pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.50,0:14:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then why not say a pen?\NWhy... why say ''iron pen''?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.54,0:14:51.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cos it's a prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.58,0:14:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute. ''lron pen'' - the ''iron''\Ndoes not describe the ink in the pen,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.38,0:14:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it describes what was penned.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.18,0:15:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt was ''iron'' -\Nit was firm, it was mineral...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.34,0:15:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no, that's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.02,0:15:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt was... lt was firm,\Nit was adamant, it was resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.98,0:15:12.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt was resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.62,0:15:15.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Mr Matlack can't offend.''
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.62,0:15:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Timothy Matlack was the official scribe\Nof the Continental Congress.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.18,0:15:23.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calligrapher, not writer. And to make sure\Nhe could not offend the map,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.42,0:15:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it was put on the back of a resolution\Nthat he transcribed,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.14,0:15:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a resolution that 55 men signed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.50,0:15:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Declaration of lndependence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.62,0:15:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, there's no invisible map on the\Nback of the Declaration of lndependence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.98,0:15:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's clever, really.\NA document of that importance
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.38,0:15:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would ensure the map's survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.66,0:15:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you said there were several Masons\Nsigned it, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.34,0:15:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Nine, for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.78,0:16:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to arrange a way to examine it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.26,0:16:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is one of the most important\Ndocuments in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.38,0:16:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're not just gonna let us waltz in there\Nand run chemical tests on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.70,0:16:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Then what do you propose we do?\N- l don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.82,0:16:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We could borrow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.86,0:16:20.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Steal it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.14,0:16:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- l don't think so.\N- Ben...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.98,0:16:28.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the treasure of the Knights Templar\Nis the treasure of all treasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.34,0:16:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, l didn't know that.\NReally?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.78,0:16:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Ben... l understand your bitterness.\Nl really do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.26,0:16:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've spent your entire life\Nsearching for this treasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.34,0:16:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,only to have\Nthe respected historical community
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.54,0:16:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,treat you and your family\Nwith mockery and contempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.30,0:16:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should be able to rub this treasure\Nin their arrogant faces,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.78,0:16:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and l want you to have\Nthe chance to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.30,0:16:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.18,0:16:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We all have our areas of expertise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.90,0:16:59.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't think mine are limited\Nto writing cheques, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.42,0:17:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ln another life...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.34,0:17:07.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l arranged a number of operations of...\Nquestionable legality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.29,0:17:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'd take his word for it, if l were you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.46,0:17:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So don't worry.\Nl'll make all the arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.13,0:17:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.61,0:17:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'd really need your help here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.29,0:17:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lan... l'm not gonna let you steal\Nthe Declaration of lndependence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.70,0:17:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.90,0:17:39.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From this point on\Nall you're going to be is a hindrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.78,0:17:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.62,0:17:47.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you gonna do?\NAre you gonna shoot me, Shaw?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.02,0:17:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you can't shoot me.\NThere's more to the riddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.74,0:17:53.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lnformation you don't have. l do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.94,0:17:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm the only one who can figure it out,\Nand you know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.94,0:17:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's bluffing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.26,0:18:01.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We played poker together, lan.\NYou know l can't bluff.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.90,0:18:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me what l need to know, Ben,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.22,0:18:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or l'll shoot your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.50,0:18:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.94,0:18:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet, Riley!\NYour job's finished here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.66,0:18:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look where you're standing.\NAll that gunpowder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.78,0:18:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shoot me,\Nl drop this, we all go up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.82,0:18:25.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.34,0:18:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happens when the flare burns down?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.86,0:18:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me what l need to know, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.30,0:18:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need to know...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.94,0:18:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if Shaw can catch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.46,0:18:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice try, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.94,0:18:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out, Shaw!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.14,0:19:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.94,0:19:14.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Riley, get over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.90,0:19:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What is this?\N- Smuggler's hold. Get in!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.66,0:19:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Move! Get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.10,0:19:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What?\N- Move! Get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.82,0:19:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.22,0:19:38.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, let's go!\NShe's gonna blow!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.74,0:19:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.54,0:20:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, let's go.\NBefore someone sees the smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.38,0:20:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's an lnuit village\Nabout nine miles east of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.38,0:20:57.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- lt's popular with bush pilots.\N- All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.98,0:21:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Then what are we gonna do?\N- Start making our way back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.54,0:21:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, l meant about lan. He's gonna steal\Nthe Declaration of lndependence, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.90,0:21:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.86,0:21:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ls it really so hard to believe
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.18,0:21:33.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that someone's gonna try to steal\Nthe Declaration of lndependence?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.62,0:21:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The FBl gets 1 0,000 tips a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.06,0:21:38.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're not gonna worry about\Nsomething they're sure is safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.42,0:21:40.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But anyone that can do anything\Nis gonna think we're crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.94,0:21:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone crazy enough to believe us\Nisn't gonna want to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.02,0:21:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't need someone crazy. But one\Nstep short of crazy, what do you get?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.70,0:21:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Obsessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.38,0:21:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Passionate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.46,0:22:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.14,0:22:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Dr Chase can see you now, Mr Brown.\N- Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.70,0:22:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Brown?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.02,0:22:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The family name doesn't get a lot\Nof respect in the academic community.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.30,0:22:15.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh. Being kept down by the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.62,0:22:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A very cute man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.54,0:22:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.82,0:22:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Good afternoon, gentlemen.\N- Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.50,0:22:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Abigail Chase.\N- Paul Brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.62,0:22:28.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Nice to meet you.\N- Bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.34,0:22:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you, Bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.46,0:22:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- How may l help you?\N- Your accent. Pennsylvania Dutch?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.66,0:22:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saxony German.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.54,0:22:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You're not American?\N- Oh, l am an American.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.34,0:22:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l just wasn't born here.\NPlease don't touch that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.34,0:22:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. A neat collection.\NGeorge Washington's campaign buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.86,0:22:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're missing the 1 7 89 inaugural, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.46,0:22:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- l found one once.\N- That's very fortunate for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.42,0:22:55.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you told my assistant\Nthat this was an urgent matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.34,0:22:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.46,0:22:59.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, l'm gonna get straight to the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.70,0:23:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's gonna steal\Nthe Declaration of lndependence.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.30,0:23:09.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.86,0:23:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l think l'd better put you gentlemen\Nin touch with the FBl.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.98,0:23:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We've been to the FBl.\N- And?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.86,0:23:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They assured us that the Declaration\Ncannot possibly be stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.18,0:23:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- They're right.\N- My friend and l are less certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.74,0:23:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, if we were given the privilege\Nof examining the document...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.30,0:23:28.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we would be able to tell you for certain\Nif it were actually in any danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.18,0:23:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're gonna find?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.22,0:23:37.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We believe that there's an...\Nencryption on the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.94,0:23:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- An encryption, like a code?\N- Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.78,0:23:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.78,0:23:45.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A... cartograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.74,0:23:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- A map.\N- Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.38,0:23:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A map of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.10,0:23:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The location of...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.66,0:24:00.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}..of hidden items\Nof historic and intrinsic value.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.78,0:24:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- A treasure map?\N- That's where we lost the FBl.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.22,0:24:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're treasure-hunters, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.10,0:24:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're more like treasure-protectors.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.94,0:24:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Brown, l have personally seen the back\Nof the Declaration of lndependence,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.38,0:24:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and l promise you, the only thing there\Nis a notation that reads,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.58,0:24:22.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Original Declaration of lndependence,\Ndated...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.54,0:24:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Four of July, 1 7 7 6.'' Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.34,0:24:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But no map.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.78,0:24:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.02,0:24:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.06,0:24:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's where we lost\Nthe Department of Homeland Security.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.10,0:24:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What led you to assume\Nthere's this invisible map?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.58,0:24:54.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We found an engraving\Non the stem of a 200-year-old pipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.54,0:24:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Owned by Freemasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.94,0:25:00.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- May l see the pipe?\N- We don't have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.02,0:25:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Did Big Foot take it?\N- lt was nice meeting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.90,0:25:08.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.58,0:25:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, you know,\Nthat really is a nice collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.94,0:25:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Must have taken you a long time\Nto hunt down all that history.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.10,0:25:22.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lf it's any consolation,\Nyou had me convinced.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.26,0:25:24.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.70,0:25:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l was thinking, what if we go public,\Nplaster the story all over the lnternet?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.42,0:25:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's not like\Nwe have our reputations to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.70,0:25:36.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although l don't think\Nthat's exactly gonna scare lan away.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.50,0:25:40.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1 80 years of searching,\Nand l'm three feet away.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.90,0:25:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of all the words\Nwritten here about freedom,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.46,0:25:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's a line here\Nthat's at the heart of all the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.06,0:25:50.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''But when a long train of abuses\Nand usurpations,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.50,0:25:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,pursuing invariably the same object,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.14,0:25:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,evinces a design to reduce them\Nunder absolute despotism,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.02,0:26:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is their right, it is their duty\Nto throw off such government
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.86,0:26:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and provide new guards\Nfor their future security.''
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.94,0:26:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People don't talk that way any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.18,0:26:10.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Beautiful, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.62,0:26:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- No idea what you said.\N- lt means, if there's something wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.62,0:26:18.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,those who have the ability to take action\Nhave the responsibility to take action.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.62,0:26:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm gonna steal it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.66,0:26:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.42,0:26:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm gonna steal\Nthe Declaration of lndependence.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.54,0:26:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.10,0:26:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is... huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.98,0:26:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's prison huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.58,0:26:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are gonna go to prison,\Nyou know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.90,0:26:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.30,0:26:53.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that would bother most people.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.34,0:26:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lan's gonna try and steal it. And if he\Nsucceeds, he'll destroy the Declaration.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.94,0:27:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact is, the only way to protect\Nthe Declaration is to steal it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.26,0:27:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.06,0:27:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l don't think there's a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.10,0:27:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben, for God's sakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.54,0:27:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's like stealing a national monument. OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.10,0:27:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's like stealing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.26,0:27:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt can't be done. Not shouldn't be done.\Nlt can't be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.18,0:27:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me prove it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.54,0:27:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, Ben, pay attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.18,0:27:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l've brought you to the Library of Congress.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.02,0:27:34.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Because it's the biggest library\Nin the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.58,0:27:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over 20 million books.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.74,0:27:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And they're all saying\Nthe same exact thing:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.18,0:27:41.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,listen to Riley.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.50,0:27:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What we have here, my friend,\Nis an entire layout of the archives.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.14,0:27:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Short of builders' blueprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.58,0:27:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got construction orders,\Nphone lines,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.30,0:27:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,water and sewage -\Nit's all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.10,0:27:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, when the Declaration\Nis on display, OK,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.14,0:28:02.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is surrounded by guards\Nand video monitors
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.66,0:28:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and a little family from lowa and little kids\Non their eighth-grade field trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.54,0:28:10.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And beneath an inch of bulletproof glass\Nis an army of sensors and heat monitors
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.18,0:28:14.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that will go off if someone gets too close\Nwith a high fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.18,0:28:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, when it's not on display,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.58,0:28:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is lowered into a four-foot-thick\Nconcrete, steel-plated vault...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.14,0:28:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that happens to be equipped\Nwith an electronic combination lock
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.50,0:28:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and biometric access-denial systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.54,0:28:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Thomas Edison tried and failed\Nnearly 2,000 times
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.22,0:28:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to develop the carbonised cotton-thread\Nfilament for the incandescent light bulb.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.06,0:28:41.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Edison?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.46,0:28:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When asked about it,\Nhe said, ''l didn't fail,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.54,0:28:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l found out 2,000 ways\Nhow not to make a light bulb.''
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.30,0:28:49.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he only needed to find one way\Nto make it work.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.62,0:28:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Preservation Room.\NEnjoy. Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.50,0:28:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know\Nwhat the Preservation Room is for?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.26,0:29:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Delicious jams and jellies?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.74,0:29:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. That's where they clean,\Nrepair and maintain
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.38,0:29:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all the documents\Nand the storage housings
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.22,0:29:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when they're not on display or in the vault.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.42,0:29:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, when the case needs work they take\Nit out of the vault, directly across the hall
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.62,0:29:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and into the Preservation Room.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.42,0:29:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The best time for us, or lan, to steal it\Nwould be during the gala this weekend
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.26,0:29:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when the guards are distracted\Nby the VlPs upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.34,0:29:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we'll make our way to the Preservation\NRoom, where there's much less security.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.94,0:29:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if lan...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.26,0:29:36.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Preservation...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.86,0:29:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gala, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.78,0:29:42.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This might be possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.74,0:29:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt might.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.90,0:30:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we are in.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.54,0:30:34.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There you are. Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.14,0:30:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.06,0:30:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what l want.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.74,0:31:02.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Game on.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.58,0:31:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'll buy that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.94,0:31:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.94,0:32:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This just came for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.78,0:32:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l hope it's not from Stan.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.14,0:32:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''For the woman who has everything else...\NThanks for listening. Paul Brown.''
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.46,0:33:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Abigail Chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.46,0:33:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mike.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.54,0:33:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Let's do this by the book.\N- Hallway is secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.18,0:33:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Keep the document level.\N- No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.22,0:33:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What have you got?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.26,0:33:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The heat sensor went off\Nin the Declaration frame.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.22,0:33:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Run full diagnostics,\Nthen l want them all changed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.74,0:33:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our evil plan is working.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.38,0:34:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben, are you sure that we should...?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.65,0:34:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Riley.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.46,0:34:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Can you hear me?\N- Unfortunately, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.82,0:34:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're all set in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.54,0:34:37.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to go around to the front\Nand present your invitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.78,0:34:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna have to show lD.\NGo ahead, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.69,0:34:46.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Howdy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.86,0:34:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l need your invitation\Nand your lD, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.86,0:35:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you look?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.10,0:35:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}- Not bad.\N- Mazel tov.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.06,0:35:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.38,0:35:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.90,0:36:02.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh, Mr Brown.\N- Dr Chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.26,0:36:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What are you doing here?\N- ls that that hot girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.58,0:36:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- How does she look?\N- l made a last-minute donation. A big one.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.54,0:36:13.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, on that subject,\Nthank you for your wonderful gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.18,0:36:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh, you did get it? Good.\N- Yes, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.10,0:36:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, l really couldn't accept\Nsomething like that normally, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.14,0:36:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l really want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.14,0:36:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Well, you needed it.\N- Come on, Romeo, get outta there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.34,0:36:29.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l have been wondering, though,\Nwhat the engraving indicated
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.26,0:36:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on the pipe that Big Foot took.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.02,0:36:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.78,0:36:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Here you go.\N- Oh, Dr Herbert, this is Mr Brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.98,0:36:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hi.\N- Hi there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.14,0:36:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Who's the stiff?\N- Here, why don't you let me take that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.58,0:36:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- So you can take that off his hands.\N- Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.06,0:36:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A toast, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.22,0:36:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To high treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.34,0:36:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what these men were committing\Nwhen they signed the Declaration.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.66,0:36:58.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Had we lost the war, they would have been\Nhanged, beheaded, drawn and quartered,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.78,0:37:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and - Oh! Oh, my personal favourite -\Nand had their entrails cut out and burned!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.18,0:37:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, here's to the men\Nwho did what was considered wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.02,0:37:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to do what they knew was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.26,0:37:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What they knew was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.06,0:37:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.94,0:37:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Good night.\N- Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.50,0:37:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.34,0:37:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, go! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.78,0:38:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This better work.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.54,0:38:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Clear!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.46,0:38:20.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- On.\N- Door one. 30 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.30,0:38:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How does it look?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.26,0:38:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's working.\Nlt's working...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.50,0:38:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.06,0:38:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Second door. 90 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.26,0:39:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well done, boys. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.34,0:39:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We're in the elevator.\N- OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.82,0:39:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm gonna turn off\Nthe surveillance cameras. Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.54,0:39:34.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ln five, four,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.94,0:39:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,three... Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.78,0:39:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben Gates,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.10,0:39:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you are now the lnvisible Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.58,0:39:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- l'm here.\N- Give me the letters for her password.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.34,0:39:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you got for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.02,0:39:56.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hit me with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.74,0:39:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-E-F-G...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.70,0:40:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,L-O-R-V-Y.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.02,0:40:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anagrams being listed.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.98,0:40:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.02,0:40:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Top results: ''A glove fry.''
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.66,0:40:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''A very golf.''
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.22,0:40:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Fargo levy.''
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.10,0:40:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Gravy floe. Valey frog.''
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.34,0:40:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also ''Ago fly rev.''
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.94,0:40:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Grove fly a.''
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.54,0:40:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Are fly gov.''
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.38,0:40:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Era fly gov.''
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.58,0:40:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- ''Elf gov ray.''\N- lt's ''Valley Forge''.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.74,0:40:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Valley For...''\Nl don't have that on my computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.30,0:40:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's ''Valley Forge'' -\Nshe pressed the E and L twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.38,0:40:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valley Forge was a turning point\Nin the American Revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.18,0:40:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can l marry your brain?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.82,0:40:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.54,0:40:48.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.54,0:40:56.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben, you're doing great.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.94,0:41:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben, pick it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.26,0:41:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got about one...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.66,0:41:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We own video.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.74,0:41:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- l lost my feed.\N- What?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.26,0:41:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l lost my feed, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.10,0:41:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l don't know where anyone is.\Nl have nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.14,0:41:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben, l have no...\NBen, l have nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.70,0:41:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of there.\NGet out of there now.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.38,0:41:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm taking the whole thing.\Nl'll get it out in the elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.90,0:41:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?\Nls it heavy?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.82,0:41:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shaw. Door three, one minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.58,0:42:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.38,0:42:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.46,0:42:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's shooting?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.82,0:42:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Damn.\N- He's got the bloody map!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.42,0:42:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you still there? Ben?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.06,0:42:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm in the elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.18,0:42:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- lan's here. There was, uh, shooting.\N- l hate that guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.66,0:42:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Rebecca.\NDo you have a Paul Brown on that list?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.10,0:42:38.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Paul Brown?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.58,0:42:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.22,0:42:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.82,0:43:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to steal that?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.50,0:43:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's $35.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.66,0:43:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- For this?\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.90,0:43:17.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- That's a lot.\N- Hey, l don't make the prices.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.74,0:43:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.02,0:43:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l have $32...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.62,0:43:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,57 c.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.02,0:43:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We take Visa.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.62,0:43:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Mike. Sublevel three.\Nl have an alert.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.98,0:43:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you, Ben?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.14,0:44:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Where are you?\N- Stop talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.06,0:44:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Start the van.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.18,0:44:29.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben, the...\Nthe mean Declaration lady's behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.78,0:44:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.54,0:44:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's you. Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.06,0:44:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Brown, what's going on?\NWhat's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.50,0:44:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- lt's a souvenir.\N- Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.82,0:44:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop chatting and get in the van.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.34,0:44:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Code red. Code red.\NWe have a break-in.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.30,0:44:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lock it down. Nobody leaves the building.\NGet the FBl on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.02,0:45:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Did you enjoy the party?\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.38,0:45:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh, my God.\N- Oh, my God! You did not...?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.90,0:45:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- No...\N- Security! Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.02,0:45:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Give me that!\N- lt's yours. Take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.58,0:45:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Security!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.30,0:45:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Over here! Security!\N- Got you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.78,0:45:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.82,0:45:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Viktor! Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.82,0:45:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We can't just let her go!\N- We can. Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.14,0:45:31.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Security, over here!\N- Wait. No, hold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.82,0:45:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.46,0:45:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Wha...?\N- Oh, bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.54,0:45:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What do you want?\N- Give me the document.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.98,0:45:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bad, bad, bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.58,0:45:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Let me go!\N- Just bring her!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.38,0:45:46.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! No!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.50,0:45:55.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- That's...\N- Go! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.70,0:46:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And just who might you be?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.14,0:46:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Once we catch them what do we do?\N- l'm working on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.82,0:46:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right turn, right turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.82,0:46:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you just pass me that\Ndocument? Then we can all go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.22,0:46:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.70,0:46:50.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Skidding, skidding, skidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.50,0:46:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh, no!\N- Holy Lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.94,0:47:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Help!\N- No! lf she falls, the document falls.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.86,0:47:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get me next to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.82,0:47:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Thank you.\N- No!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.78,0:47:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it. Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.18,0:47:36.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Abigail!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.50,0:47:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. Jump.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.18,0:47:53.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We lost them.\N- That's all right. This... is what we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.38,0:48:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well done, Gates. Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.30,0:48:10.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Are you all right?\N- No! Those lunatics...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.90,0:48:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You're not hurt, are you?\N- You are all lunatics!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.42,0:48:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Are you hungry?\N- What?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.98,0:48:16.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.38,0:48:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still a little on edge from being shot at,\Nbut l'll be OK. Thanks for asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.26,0:48:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well, l'm not all right. Those men\Nhave the Declaration of lndependence!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.90,0:48:26.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- She lost it?\N- They don't have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.66,0:48:31.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? OK?\NNow could you please stop shouting?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.14,0:48:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Give me that!\N- You're still shouting. lt's starting to annoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.06,0:48:40.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd do well, Dr Chase,\Nto be a bit more civilised in this instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.66,0:48:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lf this is the real one, what did they get?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.62,0:48:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A souvenir.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.42,0:48:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l thought it'd be a good idea to have\Na duplicate. lt turned out l was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.30,0:48:55.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l actually had to pay for the souvenir and\Nthe real one, so you owe me $35, plus tax.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.86,0:48:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Genius.\N- Who were those men?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.74,0:49:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just the guys we warned you\Nwere gonna steal the Declaration.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.14,0:49:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you didn't believe us.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.02,0:49:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We did the only thing we could do\Nto keep it safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.66,0:49:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Verdammt! Give me that!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.18,0:49:10.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know something?\NYou're shouting again.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.46,0:49:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm pretty sure she was swearing, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.42,0:49:15.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we probably deserve that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.66,0:49:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.82,0:49:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen, my name is\NPeter Sadusky. l'm the agent in charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.06,0:49:30.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l wanna reassure you,\Nyou are not in danger in any way.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.10,0:49:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lf we all cooperate, we'll get through this\Nwith as little frustration as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.14,0:49:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.26,0:49:43.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get positive lDs. Search everyone,\Nincluding the security staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.86,0:49:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lf they refuse,\Ndetain them and get warrants.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.62,0:49:48.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Agent Hendricks?\NYou have something?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.74,0:49:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.46,0:49:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- This isn't a day for ''Um...''\N- We got a tip several days ago
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.82,0:49:57.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that someone was going to steal\Nthe Declaration of lndependence.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.82,0:50:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do we have a name on the tipster?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.70,0:50:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no file opened.\NWe didn't find the information credible.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.70,0:50:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about now?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.42,0:50:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is not a treasure map on the back\Nof the Declaration of lndependence.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.38,0:50:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there's no chance\Nanyone can steal this either.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.10,0:50:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l levelled with you 1 00 per cent.\NEverything l told you was the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.42,0:50:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l want that document, Mr Brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.90,0:50:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, my name's not Brown.\Nlt's Gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.58,0:50:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l levelled with you 98 per cent.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.94,0:50:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute, did you just say ''Gates''?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.50,0:50:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gates?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.14,0:50:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're that family with the conspiracy\Ntheory about the Founding Fathers?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.62,0:50:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- lt's not a conspiracy theory.\N- Per se.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.90,0:50:42.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what? l take it back.\NYou're not liars. You're insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.66,0:50:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a copy of the Declaration\Non display now?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.86,0:50:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yes, we decided to...\N- Leave it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.02,0:50:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The guests know something happened,\Nbut they don't know what.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.62,0:50:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They got him with a Taser at the service\Nentrance. He doesn't remember a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.74,0:50:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, we found bullet casings.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.86,0:50:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did we get a description\Nfrom the other guards?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.50,0:50:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Which guards?\N- The guards that were fired upon.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.46,0:51:03.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There weren't any other guards\Non patrol down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.74,0:51:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.90,0:51:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who was shooting,\Nwho were they shooting at,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.06,0:51:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and why weren't they getting along?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.38,0:51:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't seriously intend\Nto run chemical tests
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.18,0:51:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on the Declaration of lndependence\Nin the back of a moving van.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.30,0:51:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a clean-room environment\Nall set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.98,0:51:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,EDS suits, a particulate air filtration\Nsystem, the whole shebang.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.14,0:51:24.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Really?\N- We can't go back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.66,0:51:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.42,0:51:29.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the guy. Dr Herbert said\NDr Chase introduced him as Mr Brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.18,0:51:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not on the guestlist.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.50,0:51:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, the gift-store clerk - she said\Nhe seemed... Well, she said ''flustered''.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.54,0:51:38.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He tried to walk out with a copy\Nof the Declaration of lndependence
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.46,0:51:40.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,without paying.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.42,0:51:42.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He paid with a Visa.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.38,0:51:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Charge to Benjamin Gates.''
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.50,0:51:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A credit-card slip?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.18,0:51:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dude, we're on the grid.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.86,0:51:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll have your records from forever.\NThey'll have my records from forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.66,0:51:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l know. l know. lt's only a matter of minutes\Nbefore the FBl shows up at my front door.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.14,0:51:58.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.18,0:52:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We need those letters.\N- What letters?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.18,0:52:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, get off the road,\Ntake a right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.14,0:52:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What letters?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.74,0:52:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have the original Silence Dogood\Nletters? Did you steal those, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.66,0:52:14.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have scans of the originals.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.74,0:52:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Quiet, please.\N- How'd you get scans?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.54,0:52:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, l know the person\Nwho has the originals. Now shush.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.86,0:52:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Why do you need them?\N- She really can't shut her mouth, can she?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.14,0:52:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'll tell you what, look.\Nl will let you hold onto this
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.78,0:52:34.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if you'll promise to shut up, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.54,0:52:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.66,0:52:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Ben, you know what you have to do.\N- l know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.06,0:52:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm just trying to think\Nof anything else we could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.74,0:52:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, not to be a... nudge,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.42,0:52:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you do realise how many people\Nwe have after us.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.34,0:52:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We probably have\Nour own satellite by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.62,0:52:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt took you all of two seconds to decide\Nto steal the Declaration of lndependence.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.94,0:53:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but l didn't think l was gonna\Npersonally have to tell my dad about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.78,0:53:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, not cool! Not cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.42,0:53:07.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.50,0:53:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK. You're let go. Go, shoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.78,0:53:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm not going. Not without the Declaration.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.06,0:53:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going with the Declaration.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.94,0:53:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, l am. l'm not letting it\Nout of my sight, so l'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.54,0:53:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. You're not going with us\Nwith the Declaration.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.70,0:53:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yes, l am.\N- No, you're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.86,0:53:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, if you wanted to leave me behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.06,0:53:31.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you shouldn't have told me\Nwhere you were going.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.42,0:53:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.02,0:53:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.58,0:53:55.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we're getting somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.14,0:53:59.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They're digital scans of letters\Nto the editor of The New England Courant.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.90,0:54:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Written 1 7 22.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.58,0:54:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all from the same person.\N''Your humble servant, Silence Dogood.''
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.70,0:54:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gentlemen...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.66,0:54:27.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why is this word capitalised?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.70,0:54:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's important?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.54,0:54:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.86,0:54:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, l got it.\NWhen Ben Franklin was only 1 5 years old
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.82,0:54:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he secretly wrote 1 4 letters\Nto his brother's newspaper
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.70,0:54:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,pretending to be a middle-aged widow\Nnamed Silence Dogood.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.30,0:54:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These letters were written\Nby Benjamin Franklin.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.58,0:54:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.94,0:54:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Park a couple of blocks away.\N- Well, how long do you think we got?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.54,0:55:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm gonna give them a couple of hours\Nat least. l hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.06,0:55:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do about her?\Nl've got some duct tape in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.98,0:55:09.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that won't be necessary.\NShe won't be any trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.22,0:55:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Promise you won't be any trouble.\N- l promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.38,0:55:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? She's curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.90,0:55:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's what l got on Gates. A degree\Nin American History from Georgetown,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.30,0:55:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a degree in Mechanical Engineering\Nat MlT,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.46,0:55:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Navy ROTC and Naval Diving\Nand Salvage Training Centre.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.50,0:55:31.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world did this guy\Nwant to be when he grew up?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.18,0:55:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We keep our focus on Gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.18,0:55:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Run him to ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.46,0:55:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Compile a family-and-friends list.\NClosest relative first.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.54,0:55:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l want to find out who this guy is.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.54,0:55:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.06,0:55:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the party?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.50,0:56:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... l'm in a little trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.14,0:56:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- ls she pregnant?\N- Well, if she is,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.74,0:56:08.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are you gonna leave the woman carrying\Nyour grandchild standing out in the cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.10,0:56:11.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l look pregnant?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.90,0:56:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This better not be about\Nthat dumb treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.06,0:56:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, have a seat.\NMake yourselves comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.66,0:56:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's some pizza.\Nlt's still warm, l think.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.46,0:56:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.86,0:56:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l need the Silence Dogood letters.\NYeah, it's about the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.66,0:56:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he dragged you two\Ninto this nonsense?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.70,0:56:42.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Literally.\N- l volunteered.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.14,0:56:46.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, unvolunteer,\Nbefore you waste your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.30,0:56:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Knock it off, Dad.\N- Sure, sure, l know, l'm the family kook.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.30,0:56:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l have a job, a house, health insurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.54,0:56:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least l had your mother, for however\Nbrief a time. At least l had you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.62,0:56:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you have? Him?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.94,0:57:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, if you just give us the letters,\Nwe're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.06,0:57:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You disappoint me, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.98,0:57:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, maybe that's the real Gates-family\Nlegacy. Sons who disappoint their fathers.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.30,0:57:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out. Take your troubles with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.02,0:57:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}l found the Charlotte.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.66,0:57:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Charlotte?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.38,0:57:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You mean she was a ship?\N- Yeah, she was beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.22,0:57:32.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt was amazing, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.26,0:57:34.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.98,0:57:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no. But we found another clue\Nthat led us here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.70,0:57:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, and that'll lead you\Nto another clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.34,0:57:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's all you'll ever find,\Nis another clue. Don't you get it, Ben?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.90,0:57:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l finally figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.38,0:57:47.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The legend says that the treasure\Nwas buried to keep it from the British.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.54,0:57:50.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what really happened\Nwas the legend was invented,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.26,0:57:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to keep the British occupied\Nsearching for buried treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.42,0:57:57.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The treasure is a myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.62,0:57:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l refuse to believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.86,0:58:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you can believe what you want.\NYou're a grown person. What am l doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.02,0:58:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do what you want, Ben.\NDo what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.58,0:58:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's probably right. You don't even know\Nif there is another clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.10,0:58:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, l can think of a way where we could\Nfind out. And we can find out right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.82,0:58:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like animal skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.46,0:58:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- How old is it?\N- At least 200 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.54,0:58:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Really? You sure?\N- Pretty darn.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.18,0:58:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now if this thing's in invisible ink,\Nhow do we look at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.66,0:58:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Throw it in the oven.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.98,0:58:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- No.\N- Uh-uh.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.58,0:58:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ferrous sulphate inks\Ncan only be brought out with heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.22,0:59:02.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yes, but this...\N- lt's very old.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.34,0:59:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is very old, and we can't\Nrisk compromising the map.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.90,0:59:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need a reagent.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.10,0:59:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, it's really late.\NWhy don't you get some rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.78,0:59:14.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.26,0:59:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lemons.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.34,0:59:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You can't do that.\N- But it has to be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.66,0:59:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then someone who is trained to handle\Nantique documents is gonna do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.70,0:59:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.30,0:59:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.06,0:59:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, if there is a secret message,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.02,0:59:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it'll probably be marked by a symbol\Nin the upper right-hand corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.22,0:59:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.38,0:59:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l am so getting fired for this.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.86,1:00:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l told you. You need heat.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.78,1:00:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.98,1:00:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We need more juice.\N- We need more heat.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.94,1:01:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not a map.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.30,1:01:07.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- ls it?\N- More clues. What a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.42,1:01:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are those latitudes and longitudes?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.10,1:01:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we need\Nthe Silence Dogood letters.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.58,1:01:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- That's the key?\N- Yeah. ''The key in Silence undetected.''
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.62,1:01:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, can we have the letters now?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.26,1:01:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will somebody please explain to me\Nwhat these magic numbers are?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.66,1:01:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- lt's an Ottendorf cipher.\N- That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.02,1:01:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.86,1:01:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What's an Ottendorf cipher?\N- They're just codes.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.74,1:01:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each of these three numbers\Ncorresponds to a word in a key.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.98,1:01:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Usually a random book\Nor a newspaper article.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.74,1:01:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ln this case,\Nthe Silence Dogood letters.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.86,1:01:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's like the page number\Nof the key text,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.30,1:01:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the line on the page,\Nand the letter in that line.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.50,1:01:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Dad, where are the letters?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.14,1:01:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, it's just by sheer happenstance\Nthat his grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.98,1:01:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}- Dad.\N- ..even found them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.18,1:01:53.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were in an antique desk\Nfrom the press room...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.46,1:01:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}- Dad.\N- ..of The New England Courant.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.14,1:01:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- That's a newspaper.\N- Dad, where are the letters?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.14,1:02:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l don't have them, son.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.90,1:02:03.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What?\N- l don't have them.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.10,1:02:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are they?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.50,1:02:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l donated them to the Franklin lnstitute\Nin Philadelphia.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.42,1:02:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Time to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.34,1:02:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l still can't believe it. All this time\Nno one knew what was on the back.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.90,1:02:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The back of what?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.34,1:02:26.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.46,1:02:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh, my God. Oh, my God.\N- l know.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.98,1:02:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God. What have you done?\NThis is... this is the...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.54,1:02:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- l know!\N- This is the Declaration of lndependence.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.22,1:02:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. And it's very delicate.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.34,1:02:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You stole it?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.54,1:02:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, l can explain, but l don't have time.\Nlt was necessary. And you saw the cipher.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.74,1:02:47.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that will lead to another clue,\Nand that will lead to another clue!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.42,1:02:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no treasure.\Nl wasted 20 years of my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.78,1:02:53.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now you've destroyed yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.30,1:02:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you pulled me into all this.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.14,1:02:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we can't have that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.26,1:03:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come in!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.82,1:03:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.66,1:03:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FBl, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.30,1:03:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gonna untie me?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.14,1:03:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you have no idea where he's going?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.62,1:03:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Well, wouldn't l have told you if l did?\N- Would you?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.58,1:03:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He tied me to a chair.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.74,1:03:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The garage is empty, but there's a Cadillac\NDe Ville registered to Patrick Gates.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.66,1:03:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he stole my car.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.06,1:03:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, Mr Gates, we'll find your car.\NAnd your son.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.10,1:03:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your dad's got a sweet ride.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.42,1:03:46.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l think we should change clothes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.22,1:03:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We look kind of conspicuous,\Ndon't you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.74,1:03:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'd love to go shopping, too,\Nbut we have no money.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.70,1:03:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, l took this from his house.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.70,1:03:57.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He usually tucks a few hundred dollars\Nsomewhere between those pages.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.34,1:04:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}- Common Sense. How appropriate.\N- When are we gonna get there?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.42,1:04:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm hungry. This car smells weird.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.50,1:04:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.66,1:04:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. Oops, sorry, sir. Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.54,1:04:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.66,1:05:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-S-A-N-D.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.78,1:05:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.74,1:05:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure this is right?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.70,1:05:10.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.10,1:05:12.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-S-A...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.86,1:05:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, N.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.66,1:05:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- That is an N.\N- lt doesn't look like an N.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.62,1:05:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what? Here. Last one. OK?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.98,1:05:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- One more dollar.\N- Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.66,1:05:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go get the last four letters.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.82,1:05:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go get 'em, chief. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.50,1:05:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK. ''The vision to see the treasured past
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.82,1:05:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,comes as the timely shadow crosses\Nin front of the house of pass and...''
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.06,1:06:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Pass and...'' what?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.54,1:06:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Pass and...''
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.10,1:06:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.54,1:06:49.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- l'm not sure.\N- What's up?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.78,1:06:54.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you show up at your father's door\Nand say you're in trouble
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.18,1:06:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the first thing he assumes\Nis l'm pregnant.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.94,1:07:01.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ls there a question in there?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.30,1:07:03.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l think there's an interesting story\Nin there.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.82,1:07:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, my father thinks l've been\Na little too cavalier in my personal life.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.78,1:07:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- l see.\N- Let me ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.46,1:07:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever told someone -\Nnot a relative - ''l love you''?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.34,1:07:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.54,1:07:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More than one someone?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.94,1:07:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.42,1:07:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Well, then my father would say
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.30,1:07:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you've been a little too cavalier\Nin your personal life, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.62,1:07:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you get your sense of absolute certainty\Nfrom him, do you?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.02,1:07:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, l'm sure l don't know\Nwhat you mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.94,1:07:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you're certain the treasure is real,\Ndespite what anyone else thinks.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.58,1:07:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, but l hope it's real.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.10,1:07:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l mean, l've dreamt it's real\Nsince my grandfather told me about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.50,1:07:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But l want to hold it.\Nl feel like l'm so close, l can taste it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.70,1:07:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But l just... l just want to know it's not just\Nsomething in my head or in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.02,1:07:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People don't really talk that way, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.90,1:07:59.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l know. But they think that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.26,1:08:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.22,1:08:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Did you get it? Riley?\N- Oh, l got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.22,1:08:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''The vision to see\Nthe treasured past comes
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.86,1:08:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as the timely shadow crosses\Nin front of the house of Pass and Stow.''
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.06,1:08:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, ''Pass and Stow'', of course,\Nreferring to...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.86,1:08:22.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- The Liberty Bell.\N- Why do you have to do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.66,1:08:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, John Pass and John Stow\Ncast the bell.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.18,1:08:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK. Well, then, what does\Nthe rest of this mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.29,1:08:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait... ''The vision to see the treasured\Npast'' must refer to a way to read the map.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.90,1:08:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, l thought the cipher was the map.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.45,1:08:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the cipher was a way\Nto find the way to read the map.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.29,1:08:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the way to read the map can be found
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.94,1:08:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where the ''timely shadow'' crosses\Nin front of the Liberty Bell.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.37,1:08:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crosses in front of the ''house''\Nof the Liberty Bell. lndependence Hall.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.62,1:08:49.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, so ''timely shadow'' -\Nit's a specific time.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.45,1:08:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Right.\N- What time?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.49,1:08:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What time? What time?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.86,1:08:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute, wait.\NYou're gonna love this.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.98,1:09:02.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, can l see one of those\Nhundred-dollar bills l paid you with?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.58,1:09:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.54,1:09:07.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Well, here,\Nl have this diver's watch.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.98,1:09:10.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's called a Submariner. l dive with it.\Nlt's actually quite valuable.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.70,1:09:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You can use it as collateral.\N- Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.78,1:09:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.29,1:09:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the back of a hundred-dollar bill\Nis an etching of lndependence Hall
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.98,1:09:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- based on a painting done in...\N- Hello.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.62,1:09:20.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Thank you.\N..in the 1 7 80s, who...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.90,1:09:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The artist was actually a friend\Nof Benjamin Franklin's. lt's wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.25,1:09:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Fascinating.\N- Hold this.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.90,1:09:27.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.25,1:09:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm not going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.78,1:09:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, l think that if we look\Nat this clock tower...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.33,1:09:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}..we may find the specific time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.62,1:09:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What do you see?\N- 2:22.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.74,1:09:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What time is it now?\N- Almost three.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.18,1:09:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We missed it.\N- No, we didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.41,1:09:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't miss it because...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.22,1:09:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know this? l-l know something\Nabout history that you don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.42,1:10:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'd be very excited to learn about it, Riley.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.46,1:10:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, hold on one second, let me just...\Nlet me just take in this moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.70,1:10:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is... this is cool.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.22,1:10:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ls this how you feel all the time? Because,\Nyou know... Except for now, of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.94,1:10:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Riley!\N- All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.98,1:10:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What l know is that daylight savings\Nwasn't established until World War l.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.18,1:10:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lf it's 3pm now, OK, that means\Nin 1 7 7 6, it would be 2pm.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.66,1:10:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Let's go.\N- Riley, you're a genius.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.62,1:10:26.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.90,1:10:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you actually know who the first person\Nto suggest daylight savings was?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.42,1:10:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Benjamin Franklin.\N- Benjamin Franklin.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.66,1:10:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ls this real?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.78,1:10:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just tell me what you told my friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.06,1:10:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a bunch of letters.\Nl can't remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.70,1:10:45.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you remember which ones\Nyou were gonna tell him next?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.06,1:10:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, here. S-T-O-W.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.42,1:11:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Top results: Liberty Bell\Nand lndependence Hall.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.82,1:11:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lmagine its impact\Nback in the 1 8th century.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.30,1:11:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt could have been seen for miles around,\Nwhich was exactly its purpose,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.30,1:11:15.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because it served as a beacon, as it were,\Nfor people to collect and hear...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.18,1:11:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.18,1:11:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt gained a place in history\Non July 8, 1 7 7 6,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.82,1:11:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when the Liberty Bell tolled\Nfor the first public reading
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.22,1:11:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of the Declaration of lndependence.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.82,1:11:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, it was moved from its place
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.94,1:11:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in lndependence Hall steeple\Nand given its own...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.38,1:11:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- ldiot.\N- Who?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.98,1:11:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Me.\N- What?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.50,1:11:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's not here. lt's there.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.26,1:11:55.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.34,1:12:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What bell is this?\N- lt's the Centennial Bell.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.66,1:12:08.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt replaced the Liberty Bell in 1 8 7 6.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.34,1:12:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.38,1:12:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. l'm gonna go down there,\Nand you meet me in the signing room.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.70,1:12:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- OK? All right.\N- OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.02,1:12:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.38,1:12:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3:22. My idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.46,1:13:36.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. What'd you score?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.38,1:13:37.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l found this.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.90,1:13:40.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some kind of ocular device.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.38,1:13:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''The vision to see the treasured past.''\NLet me take this.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.74,1:13:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, they're like early American\NX-ray specs.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.38,1:13:51.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Benjamin Franklin invented\Nsomething like these.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.42,1:13:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l think he invented these.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.70,1:13:55.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do we do with them?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.14,1:13:58.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We look through it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.94,1:14:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, help me.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.22,1:14:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Careful.\N- You think?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.58,1:14:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What?\N- lt's just that the last time this was here
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.94,1:14:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it was being signed.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.70,1:14:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Ben, there's another tour coming.\N- Turn it over.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.26,1:14:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Careful.\N- Spectacles.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.62,1:14:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.22,1:14:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? ls it a treasure map?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.82,1:14:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt says, ''Heere at the wall'',\Nspelled with two E's.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.62,1:14:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.38,1:14:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.02,1:15:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't they just say, ''Go to this place,\Nand here's the treasure, spend it wisely''?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.50,1:15:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.54,1:15:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh, no.\N- Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.78,1:15:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How'd they find us?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.30,1:15:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, lan has nearly unlimited resources.\NAnd he's smart.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.78,1:15:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l don't think we can get out of here\Nwithout being spotted.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.38,1:15:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we don't want them to have\Nthe Declaration, or the glasses.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.26,1:15:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we especially don't want them\Nto have them both together.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.86,1:15:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- So what do we do?\N- We separate the lock from the key.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.78,1:15:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We're splitting up.\N- Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.82,1:15:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.02,1:15:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'll take this.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.22,1:15:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And those. You keep that. Meet me at the\Ncar and call me if you have any problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.78,1:15:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like if we get caught and killed?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.74,1:15:40.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. That would be a big problem.\NTake care of her.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.22,1:15:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- l will.\N- l will.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.66,1:15:53.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're on him.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.74,1:15:57.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.38,1:16:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Let's walk this way.\N- Wait up.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.42,1:16:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Shaw, look. There's the others.\N- l got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.02,1:16:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Viktor, meet me at Fifth and Chestnut. Fifth\Nand Chestnut. They're heading your way.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.02,1:16:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Look out! Look out!\N- Riley!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.66,1:16:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- There they are! Move!\N- Move!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.30,1:16:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Time to run.\N- Keep up, Viktor! Move. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.50,1:16:54.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ln here.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.54,1:17:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Come on.\N- Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.74,1:17:08.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That way.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.22,1:17:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lf you're not a steak,\Nyou don't belong here.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.78,1:17:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm just trying to hide\Nfrom my ex-husband.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.02,1:17:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Who, baldy?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.30,1:17:27.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honey, stay as long as you like.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.42,1:17:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thank you. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.74,1:17:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want something?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.46,1:17:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Do you want something?\N- Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.62,1:17:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l see why you left him.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.94,1:17:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go around. Go around.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.34,1:17:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gates!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.86,1:18:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.22,1:18:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Where were you?\N- Hiding.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.66,1:18:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. Let's go, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.74,1:18:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lan. lan, l've got 'em.\NThey're heading toward City Hall.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.70,1:18:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- OK, l'm on my way.\N- Out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.54,1:19:20.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're headed for the breezeway\Non the north side.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.26,1:19:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.22,1:19:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Gates!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.74,1:19:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough, man! Give me the document.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.06,1:19:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, Phil.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.34,1:20:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out! Get out of my way!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.74,1:20:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch it!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.94,1:20:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave them! Let 'em go.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.94,1:20:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.26,1:20:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- FBl. Have you seen this guy?\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.74,1:21:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, l haven't seen him.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.54,1:21:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ted. Philadelphia police\Nfound Gates's car.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.46,1:21:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's close.\NWe got surveillance there now.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.82,1:21:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go. Tell the boss\Nwe got the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.86,1:21:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What?\N- We lost it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.46,1:21:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What?\N- We lost the Declaration. lan took it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.06,1:21:22.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, OK. You all right?\NYou both all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.14,1:21:25.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah, we're all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.22,1:21:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Ben, l'm sorry.\N- We'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.38,1:21:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meet me at the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.46,1:21:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suspect has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.50,1:21:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Mr Gates.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.58,1:21:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Gates, face your father's car and\Nput your hands behind your back, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.74,1:21:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We got one in custody.\N- Gates, you're a hard man to find.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.26,1:21:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you please be careful?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.46,1:22:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Riley, do you know\Nhow to get in touch with lan?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.82,1:22:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.86,1:22:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's some story.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.06,1:22:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's the same story l tried to tell you\Nguys before the Declaration was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.66,1:22:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- By you.\N- No, by lan. l stole it to stop him.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.42,1:22:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l did it alone.\NDr Chase was not involved.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.10,1:22:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And lan still ended up with\Nthe Declaration of lndependence.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.38,1:22:35.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.94,1:22:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So here's your options.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.82,1:22:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Door number one,\Nyou go to prison for a very long time.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.22,1:22:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Door number two, we are going to get back\Nthe Declaration of lndependence,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.14,1:22:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you help us find it, and you still\Ngo to prison for a very long time,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.82,1:22:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you feel better inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.22,1:22:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ls there a door that doesn't lead to prison?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.26,1:23:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Someone's got to go to prison, Ben.\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.66,1:23:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what are these for?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.94,1:23:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's a way to read the map.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.94,1:23:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.66,1:23:12.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knights Templar.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.18,1:23:13.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Freemasons.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.66,1:23:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lnvisible treasure map.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.66,1:23:20.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- So what'd it say?\N- ''Heere at the wall.''
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.34,1:23:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.82,1:23:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's just another clue.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.30,1:23:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt looks like lan Howe\Ncould be a false identity.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.86,1:23:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Follow up with ATF and lNS.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.94,1:23:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's more to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.38,1:23:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Standard tap procedure.\N- Let's check the signal, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.86,1:23:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Lock it in.\N- Are we set?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.18,1:23:41.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Checking source.\N- Unknown number.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.18,1:23:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.46,1:23:47.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Ben. How are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.10,1:23:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Um, chained to a desk.\N- Sorry to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.90,1:23:54.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}l want you to meet me on the flight deck\Nof the USS Intrepid.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.50,1:23:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You know where that is?\N- New York.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.94,1:23:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meet me there at ten o'clock\Ntomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.94,1:24:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And bring those glasses\Nyou found at lndependence Hall.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.38,1:24:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, l know about the glasses.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.58,1:24:09.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can take a look at the Declaration,\Nand then you can be on your way.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.42,1:24:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And l'm supposed to believe that.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.22,1:24:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l told you from the start,\Nl only wanted to borrow it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.30,1:24:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can have it. And the glasses.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.22,1:24:19.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}l'll even throw in the pipe\Nfrom the Charlotte.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.94,1:24:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'll be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.66,1:24:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And tell the FBl agents\Nlistening in on this call
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.66,1:24:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if they want the Declaration back,\Nand not just a box of confetti,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.50,1:24:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then you'll come alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.26,1:24:45.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Take positions.\N- Perimeter looks normal.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.02,1:24:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Can l get a status report?\N- Crow's nest in position. Port side is quiet.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.34,1:24:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Copy that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.46,1:25:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Gates is on the flight deck.\N- Eyes on Gates.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.02,1:25:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Do not lose sight of primary mark.\N- Brian, you're clear with NYPD.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.18,1:25:09.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- l have a visual.\N- Gates.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.70,1:25:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay with the program.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.94,1:25:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l hope your agents are all under four feet\Ntall and wearing little scarves.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.18,1:25:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise lan's gonna know they're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.10,1:25:18.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as he shows you the Declaration,\Nwe'll move in.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.90,1:25:21.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't try anything.\NJust let us handle it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.46,1:25:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Agent Sadusky,\Nsomething l've noticed about fishing:
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.54,1:25:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it never works out so well for the bait.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.50,1:25:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, we've got some traffic incoming.\NLooks like a sightseeing helicopter.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.26,1:25:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unit two,\Nget an eyeball on that chopper.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.62,1:25:44.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Agent Michaels, get FAA flight plans\Nand authorization records on that craft.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.02,1:25:48.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lf that's not Mr Howe,\Nl want to know who it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.30,1:25:52.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- l got him. He's coming from the north.\N- Gates. Are you with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.42,1:25:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, l'm sure not against you,\Nif that's what you're asking.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.34,1:26:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got some interference\Non Gates's mike, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.74,1:26:21.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This l know.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.30,1:26:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.82,1:26:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thomas Edison needed only one way\Nto make a light bulb.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.22,1:26:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sound familiar?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.46,1:26:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Keep sightlines clear.\N- What's the devil's going on?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.66,1:26:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a lot of commotion.\NWe can't see Gates.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.34,1:26:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go to the starboard observation point\Nbehind the F-1 6 and here's what you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.42,1:26:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gates? Gates?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.82,1:26:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Air Tour helicopter,\Nyou are in controlled airspace.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.38,1:26:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vacate immediately.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.98,1:26:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's got Gates?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.58,1:26:53.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- All agents, report in.\N- l can't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.90,1:26:56.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Did Gates speak to anybody?\N- Target is moving.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.18,1:27:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- He's heading towards the stern.\N- l've got him. He's coming this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.06,1:27:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone got a view of our friend lan Howe?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.18,1:27:04.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lan Howe is not at the stern, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.06,1:27:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why is he heading there?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.22,1:27:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's at the observation deck.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.34,1:27:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sadusky.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.78,1:27:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm still not against you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.70,1:27:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But l found door number three.\NAnd l'm taking it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.46,1:27:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What's he talking about?\N- Move in!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.50,1:27:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Move in! Move in on Gates!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.26,1:27:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Divers are a go.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.30,1:27:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Snipers, go to action zebra.\N- All teams, move in. Pursue at own risk.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.98,1:27:38.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- l repeat, pursue at own risk.\N- You first.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.70,1:27:41.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Holy mackerel. He set us up.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.62,1:28:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Agent Dawes, do you have a visual?\NCan you see Gates in the water?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.30,1:28:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, it's the Hudson. Nothing is visible.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.70,1:28:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Smart fish.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.30,1:28:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Ben. Welcome to New Jersey.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.66,1:28:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What'd you do with Abigail and Riley?\N- Hope these fit.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.18,1:28:37.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We had to guess your sizes.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.74,1:28:39.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l said, what'd you do\Nwith Abigail and Riley?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.74,1:28:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the only one who could've\Ntold you that line about Edison.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.98,1:28:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you bring the glasses?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.94,1:28:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l don't know.\NTell me what's happening here.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.78,1:28:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ask your girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.34,1:28:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's the one calling all the shots now.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.78,1:28:53.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She won't shut up.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.58,1:28:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, hello.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.02,1:29:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.66,1:29:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hello.\N- Hi, sweetie. How's your day going?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.50,1:29:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, interesting, dear.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.58,1:29:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what, you working with lan now?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.54,1:29:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt turns out helping someone escape\Nfrom FBl custody is a criminal act.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.42,1:29:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he's the only criminal we knew.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.94,1:29:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- So we called him and made a deal.\N- Well, you're...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.22,1:29:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're... you're... you're all right, yeah?\Nl mean you're safe?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.86,1:29:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we both are.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.14,1:29:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Riley's right here, doing\Nsomething clever with a computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.50,1:29:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm tracking him through the... Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.58,1:29:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm tracking you through the GPS\Nin Shaw's phone.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.98,1:29:35.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They take a turn anywhere we don't want,\Nwe'll know it. So don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.18,1:29:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lf lan tries to double-cross us, we can call\Nthe FBl and tell them right where you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.54,1:29:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- And where to find lan.\N- And where is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.30,1:29:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right across the street\Nfrom where we're hiding,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.50,1:29:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at the intersection\Nof Wall Street and Broadway.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.94,1:29:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you figured out the clue.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.30,1:29:54.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Simple. ''Heere at the wall.''\NWall Street and Broadway.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.54,1:29:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben, there is a catch.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.62,1:30:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We made lan believe\Nhe could have the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.62,1:30:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt was the only way\Nwe could get this far.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.58,1:30:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's here.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.82,1:30:15.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.26,1:30:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.34,1:30:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You all right? No broken bones?\NA jump like that could kill a man.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.34,1:30:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naw, it was cool.\NYou should try it sometime.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.38,1:30:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Declaration of lndependence.\NAnd the meerschaum pipe.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.58,1:30:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.34,1:30:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- That's it?\N- That's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.70,1:30:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l knew you'd keep your promise.\NNow, where is it? Where's my treasure?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.82,1:30:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.58,1:30:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The map said ''Heere at the wall'',\Nspelled with two E's.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.74,1:30:53.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wall Street follows the path\Nof an actual wall
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.46,1:30:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the original Dutch settlers built\Nas a defence to keep the British out.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.50,1:31:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The main gate was located at a street\Ncalled De Heere, also two E's.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.94,1:31:03.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Later De Heere Street was renamed\NBroadway after the British got in.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.58,1:31:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, ''Heere at the wall.''
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.10,1:31:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Broadway, Wall Street.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.46,1:31:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheerio.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.54,1:31:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a moment, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.26,1:31:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lan, if you break our deal, the FBl\Nwill be only a few minutes behind you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.94,1:31:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might get away, you might not.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.10,1:31:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ls that all the map said?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.14,1:31:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every word.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.10,1:31:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.42,1:31:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know the key\Nto running a convincing bluff?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.62,1:31:42.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every once in a while\Nyou've got to be holding all the cards.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.78,1:31:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.70,1:31:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ls there anything else you want to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.34,1:32:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trinity Church. We have to go\Ninside Trinity Church.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.86,1:32:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.14,1:32:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, why don't you ask Dr Chase\Nand Riley to join us?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.06,1:32:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm sure they're around here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.10,1:32:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.58,1:32:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think? l'm a hostage.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.42,1:32:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sit. Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.70,1:32:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Let him go, lan.\N- When we find the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.78,1:32:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, now. Or you can figure out\Nthe clues for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.02,1:32:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.86,1:32:42.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.30,1:32:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l don't think you fully appreciate\Nthe gravity of the situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.14,1:32:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have a look at that map.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.14,1:33:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.54,1:33:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's... it's really quite something. lt's...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.22,1:33:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt really is remarkable. Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.74,1:33:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- ''Parkington Lane.''\N- ''Beneath Parkington Lane.''
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.70,1:33:53.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would the map lead us here,\Nthen take us somewhere else?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.62,1:33:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What's the purpose?\N- Just another clue.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.10,1:34:00.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad. No, you're right. Parkington Lane\Nhas to be here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.70,1:34:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A street inside the church?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.30,1:34:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not inside. Beneath.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.86,1:34:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Beneath the church.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.10,1:34:15.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- l'm so sorry, Ben.\N- None of this is your fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.58,1:34:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- l co...\N- Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.98,1:34:27.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.70,1:34:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cooperation only lasts as long\Nas the status quo is unchanged.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.58,1:34:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as this guy gets to wherever this\Nthing ends, he won't need you any more.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.38,1:34:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or... or any of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.70,1:34:42.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we find a way to make sure\Nthe status quo changes in our favour.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.42,1:34:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- How?\N- l'm still working on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.26,1:34:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, l guess l better\Nwork on it too, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.34,1:34:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Par... Hey, l found it!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.02,1:34:53.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Him!\N- Ben!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.26,1:34:56.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's a name.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.94,1:35:00.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Parkington Lane.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.70,1:35:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a third-degree master mason\Nof the Blue Lo...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.30,1:35:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.22,1:35:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Easy.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.14,1:35:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Careful no one steps in him.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.14,1:35:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, put it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.82,1:35:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK. Who wants to go down\Nthe creepy tunnel inside the tomb first?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.70,1:35:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. McGregor, Viktor, you stay here.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.46,1:35:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if anyone should come out without me,\Nwell... use your imagination.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.34,1:35:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.26,1:36:15.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got a light?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.90,1:36:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Careful.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.26,1:36:36.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch your step.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.98,1:36:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.86,1:36:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why does that never happen to me?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.94,1:37:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.70,1:37:19.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's a chandelier.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.46,1:37:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.02,1:37:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Wow.\N- Look at the elevators.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.82,1:37:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dumbwaiter system.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.42,1:37:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do a bunch of guys with hand tools\Nbuild all this?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.02,1:37:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Same way they built the pyramids\Nand the Great Wall of China.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.54,1:37:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The aliens helped them.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.62,1:38:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, let's go. What are we waiting for?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.14,1:38:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm not going out on that thing.\N200 years of termite damage and rot.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.22,1:38:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, do what he says.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.62,1:38:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch your step.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.54,1:38:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're right under the Trinity graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.46,1:38:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably why\Nno one ever found this.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.50,1:38:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.62,1:38:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Subway.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.30,1:38:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shaw! Oh, God, Shaw!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.70,1:39:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.90,1:39:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on! Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.78,1:39:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, get on the elevator. Jump!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.06,1:39:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben! Grab my hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.10,1:39:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Come on.\N- lan!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.74,1:39:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Abigail! Get on!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.98,1:39:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jump!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.94,1:39:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.90,1:39:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.22,1:39:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get down there.\NGet down there!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.94,1:40:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Declaration.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.62,1:40:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Do you trust me?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.30,1:40:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! Ben!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.02,1:40:33.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.26,1:40:43.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Son!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.46,1:40:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm sorry. l'm sorry l dropped you.\Nl had to save the Declaration.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.42,1:40:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, don't be. l would have done\Nexactly the same thing to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.86,1:41:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.98,1:41:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l would have dropped you both.\NFreaks.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.66,1:41:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get on.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.86,1:41:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lan...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.66,1:41:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's not worth it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:18.06,1:41:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you imagine any one of your lives\Nis more valuable to me than Shaw's?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.62,1:41:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We go on.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.58,1:41:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The status quo.\NKeep the status quo.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.78,1:41:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Now what?\N- This is...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.98,1:41:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is where it all leads.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.82,1:41:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.90,1:42:37.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.42,1:42:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So where's the treasure?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.54,1:42:43.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.38,1:42:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.66,1:42:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We came all this way\Nfor a dead end?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.22,1:42:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.66,1:42:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- There's gotta be something more.\N- Riley, there's nothing more.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.46,1:43:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Another clue, or...\N- No, there are no more clues!
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.82,1:43:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it, OK? lt's over!
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.46,1:43:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,End of the road. The treasure's gone.\NMoved. Taken somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.70,1:43:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not playing games with me,\Nare you, Ben? Hm?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.58,1:43:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know where it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.50,1:43:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.74,1:43:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, go.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.98,1:43:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.02,1:43:27.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hey! lan, wait!\N- Wait, wait, wait!
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.26,1:43:28.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- lan...\N- We'll be trapped.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.98,1:43:31.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Don't do this.\N- You can't just leave us here.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.42,1:43:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, l can.\NUnless Ben tells me the next clue.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.26,1:43:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't another clue.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:37.50,1:43:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lan, why don't you come back down here\Nand we can talk through this together?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.82,1:43:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Don't speak again.\N- OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.62,1:43:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The clue. Where's the treasure?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.62,1:43:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.66,1:43:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- The lantern.\N- Dad...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.98,1:44:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The status quo has changed, son.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.26,1:44:01.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.70,1:44:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's part of freemason teachings.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.46,1:44:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ln King Solomon's temple\Nthere was a winding staircase.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.82,1:44:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt signified the journey that had to be made\Nto find the light of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.62,1:44:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- The lantern is the clue.\N- And what does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.38,1:44:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Boston. lt's Boston.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.86,1:44:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Old North Church in Boston,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.54,1:44:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where Thomas Newton\Nhung a lantern in the steeple,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.02,1:44:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to signal Paul Revere that the British\Nwere coming. One if by land, two if by sea.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.86,1:44:37.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One lantern. Under the winding staircase\Nof the steeple, that's where we have to look.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.90,1:44:40.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Thank you.\N- Hey, you have to take us with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.22,1:44:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? So you can escape in Boston?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.34,1:44:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, with you out of the picture\Nthere's less baggage to carry.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.90,1:44:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if we lied?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.10,1:44:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.38,1:44:53.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if there's another clue?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.10,1:44:56.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then l'll know right where to find you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.78,1:44:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.14,1:45:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- No!\N- There's no other way out!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.90,1:45:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Come back!\N- You're gonna need us, lan!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.82,1:45:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're all gonna die.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.18,1:45:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's gonna be OK, Riley.\Nl'm sorry l yelled at you.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.14,1:45:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's OK, kiddo.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.22,1:45:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, boys, what's going on? The British\Ncame by sea. lt was two lanterns, not one.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.74,1:45:23.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lan needed another clue,\Nso we gave it to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.82,1:45:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt was a fake.\Nlt was a fake clue.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.70,1:45:29.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The all-seeing eye.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.22,1:45:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Through the all-seeing eye.''
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.34,1:45:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means... by the time lan\Nfigures it out and comes back here,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.30,1:45:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll still be trapped,\Nand he'll shoot us then.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:39.38,1:45:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, we're gonna die.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.70,1:45:45.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody's gonna die.\NThere's another way out.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.42,1:45:47.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.50,1:45:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Through the treasure room.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:56.54,1:45:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:07.82,1:46:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Riley.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:35.02,1:46:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like someone got here first.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:39.50,1:46:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm sorry, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.06,1:46:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.18,1:46:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Listen, Ben...\N- lt may have even been gone
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.86,1:46:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,before Charles Carroll\Ntold the story to Thomas Gates.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:53.74,1:46:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.86,1:46:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l know. Cos you were right.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:58.74,1:47:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, l wasn't right.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.62,1:47:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This room is real, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.26,1:47:06.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that means the treasure is real.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:06.94,1:47:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in the company of\Nsome of the most brilliant minds in history,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.70,1:47:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because you found\Nwhat they left behind for us to find
Dialogue: 0,1:47:13.46,1:47:15.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and understood the meaning of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:16.02,1:47:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did it, Ben. For all of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:19.78,1:47:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your grandfather, and all of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.46,1:47:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And l've never been so happy\Nto be proven wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.26,1:47:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l just...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.38,1:47:42.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,really thought\Nl was gonna find the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.18,1:47:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.14,1:47:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we just keep looking for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.90,1:47:53.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm in.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.38,1:48:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:01.66,1:48:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not to be Johnny Rain Cloud here,\Nbut that's not gonna happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:04.70,1:48:07.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because as far as l can see,\Nwe're still trapped down here.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.98,1:48:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.46,1:48:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Ben,\Nwhere is this other way out?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.34,1:48:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's it.\Nlt doesn't make any sense,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:14.42,1:48:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because the first thing the builders\Nwould have done after getting down here
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.58,1:48:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was cut a secondary shaft back out for air...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.62,1:48:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}- Right.\N- ..and in case of cave-ins.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.90,1:48:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it really be that simple?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.18,1:48:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''The secret lies with Charlotte.''
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.62,1:50:21.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scrolls from the library at Alexandria.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.54,1:50:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could this be possible?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:44.06,1:50:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's a big... bluish-green man,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.98,1:50:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with a strange-looking goatee.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.82,1:50:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm guessing that's significant.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:41.86,1:51:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:54.10,1:51:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Riley, are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:56.82,1:51:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:58.86,1:52:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:16.58,1:52:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.62,1:52:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a cell phone l could borrow?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.14,1:52:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Just like that?\N- Just like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:36.10,1:52:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You do know you just handed me\Nyour biggest bargaining chip?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.34,1:52:42.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Declaration of lndependence\Nis not a bargaining chip.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:42.58,1:52:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.30,1:52:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:46.42,1:52:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what's your offer?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:49.26,1:52:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about a bribe? Say...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.02,1:52:56.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ten billion dollars?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:56.26,1:52:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l take it you found the treasure?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:57.90,1:53:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's about five stories\Nbeneath your shoes.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:04.06,1:53:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, the Templars\Nand the Freemasons believed
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.18,1:53:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the treasure was too great\Nfor any one man to have, not even a king.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:10.78,1:53:14.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why they went to such lengths\Nto keep it hidden.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:14.46,1:53:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:16.82,1:53:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Founding Fathers believed\Nthe same thing about government.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:20.30,1:53:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l figure their solution\Nwill work for the treasure too.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:23.90,1:53:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give it to the people.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.02,1:53:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Divide it amongst the Smithsonian,\Nthe Louvre, the Cairo museum...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.98,1:53:32.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's thousands of years\Nof world history down there.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:33.06,1:53:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it belongs to the world,\Nand everybody in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:37.38,1:53:40.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really don't understand\Nthe concept of a bargaining chip.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:41.54,1:53:45.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, here's what l want.\NDr Chase gets off completely clean,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:46.06,1:53:48.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,not even a little Post-it\Non her service record.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.18,1:53:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.10,1:53:54.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l want the credit for the find\Nto go to the entire Gates family,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:55.10,1:53:57.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with the assistance of Mr Riley Poole.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.86,1:54:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what about you?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:00.18,1:54:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'd really love not to go to prison.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:02.22,1:54:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l can't even begin to describe\Nhow much l would love not to go to prison.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:08.14,1:54:10.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's got to go to prison, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:11.18,1:54:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if you've got a helicopter,\Nl think l can help with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:24.26,1:54:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Freeze! FBl!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:28.54,1:54:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Freeze! Don't move!\N- Show me your hands!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:32.42,1:54:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Put your hands up.\N- Move, move, move.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:39.26,1:54:40.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're under arrest, Mr Howe.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:41.14,1:54:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got you on kidnapping,\Nattempted murder...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:44.46,1:54:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and trespassing on government property.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.34,1:54:57.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. You got it, chief.\NThank you. Bye.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.14,1:55:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They want us in Cairo next week\Nfor the opening of the exhibit.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:02.10,1:55:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're sending a private jet.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.98,1:55:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:05.22,1:55:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, big whoop. We could have had\Na whole fleet of private jets.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:08.98,1:55:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten per cent, Ben. They offered you\Nten per cent and you turned it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:12.10,1:55:15.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Riley, we've been over this.\Nlt was too much. l couldn't accept it.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:15.50,1:55:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l still have this splinter that's been festering\Nfor three months from an old piece of wood.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:19.58,1:55:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, l'll tell you what.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:20.66,1:55:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time we find a treasure\Nthat redefines history for all mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:24.42,1:55:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you make the call on the finder's fee.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.42,1:55:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not as funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:28.86,1:55:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you care?\NYou got the girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.78,1:55:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- lt's true.\N- lt's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:36.70,1:55:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rub it in.\NEnjoy your spoils...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.82,1:55:41.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while l sit on one per cent.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.74,1:55:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One stinkin' per cent.\NHalf of one per cent, actually.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:46.02,1:55:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One per cent. Unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:48.42,1:55:50.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm sorry for your suffering, Riley.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:50.42,1:55:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the record, Ben,\Nl like the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:54.70,1:55:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, l chose this estate\Nbecause in 1 81 2 Charles Carroll met...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:58.06,1:56:02.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, someone that did something\Nin history and had fun. Great. Wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:02.74,1:56:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could have had a bigger house.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:12.82,1:56:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- l made something for you.\N- You did? What?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:16.46,1:56:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- A map.\N- A map?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:19.82,1:56:21.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where does it lead to?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:21.74,1:56:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:31.94,1:56:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:34.82,1:56:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
